ngdom","Dundaff Castle, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Skotsko, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1185–1247":"1185–1247","1190–1245":"1190–1245","1210–1270":"1210–1270","1190":"1190","1247":"1247","1245":"1245","before 1210":"før 1210","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1270":"1270","Fisherton, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Fisherton, Ayrshire, Skotland","Forfarshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Forfarshire, Skotland, United Kingdom","Dundaff Castle, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Skotland, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1185–1247":"1185–1247","1190–1245":"1190–1245","1210–1270":"1210–1270","1190":"1190","1247":"1247","1245":"1245","before 1210":"vóór 1210","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1270":"1270","Fisherton, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Fisherton, Ayrshire, Schotland","Forfarshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Forfarshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Dundaff Castle, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1185–1247":"1185–1247","1190–1245":"1190–1245","1210–1270":"1210–1270","1190":"1190","1247":"1247","1245":"1245","before 1210":"before 1210","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1270":"1270","Fisherton, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Fisherton, Ayrshire, Scotland","Forfarshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Forfarshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Dundaff Castle, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Graham","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from Grantham in Lincolnshire, recorded in Domesday Book as <i>Graham</i> (as well as <i>Grantham</i>, <i>Grandham</i>, and <i>Granham</i>). See also   Grantham  .","Irish (especially Ulster): in Ireland <i>Graham</i> is generally the Scottish name, but it has additionally been adopted as an Anglicized form of both <b>Ó Creacháin</b> (see   Crehan  ) and <b>Ó Gormghaile</b> (see   Gormley  ).","History: The surname Graham was taken to Scotland at the beginning of the 12th century by the Norman baron William de Graham, holder of the manor of Grantham in Lincolnshire, from whom many if not all modern bearers are probably descended. The chief of Clan Graham is the Duke of Montrose."],"variants":[{"name":"Greim","meanings":["South German: from a short form of a compound personal name beginning with the element <i>grīm</i> ‘mask, helmet’.","Scottish: variant of   Graham  ."]},{"name":"Grahm","meanings":["(1997: 107;2007: 460; 2010: NA)","Scottish (Lanarkshire and northern England): shortened form of   Graham  ."]},{"name":"Grantham","meanings":["English (Lincolnshire and East Yorkshire): habitational name from Grantham in Lincolnshire, of uncertain origin. The final element is Old English <i>hām</i> ‘homestead’; the first may be Old English <i>grand</i> ‘gravel’ or perhaps a personal name <i>Granta</i>, which probably originated as a byname meaning ‘snarler’. See also   Graham  ."]},{"name":"Grahame","meanings":["(1997: 113;2007: 164; 2010: NA)","Scottish: variant of   Graham  . — Note: The population figure published by the US Census Bureau for this surname in the year 2000 is as high as 261, while the figure for 2010 is supposedly lower than 100."]}]},{"name":"David","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by the greatest of all the kings of Israel, whose history is recounted with great vividness in the first and second books of Samuel and elsewhere. As a boy he killed the giant Philistine Goliath with his slingshot. As king of Judah, and later of all Israel, he expanded the power of the Israelites and established the security of their kingdom. He was also noted as a poet, many of the Psalms being attributed to him. The Hebrew derivation of the name is uncertain; it is said by some to represent a nursery word meaning ‘darling’. It is a very popular Jewish name, but is almost equally common among Gentiles in the English-speaking world. It is particularly common in Wales and Scotland, having been borne by the patron saint of Wales (  see  Dewi   ) and by two medieval kings of Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"David Graham was born in 1185, in Forfarshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Agnes Nobles. He died in 1247, in Fisherton, Ayrshire, Scotland, at the age of 62."},"et":{"1185–1247":"1185–1247","1190–1245":"1190–1245","1210–1270":"1210–1270","1190":"1190","1247":"1247","1245":"1245","before 1210":"enne 1210","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1270":"1270","Fisherton, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Fisherton, Ayrshire, Scotland","Forfarshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Forfarshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Dundaff Castle, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1185–1247":"1185–1247","1190–1245":"1190–1245","1210–1270":"1210–1270","1190":"1190","1247":"1247","1245":"1245","before 1210":"ennen vuotta 1210","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1270":"1270","Fisherton, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Fisherton, Ayrshire, Scotland","Forfarshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Forfarshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dundaff Castle, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1185–1247":"1185–1247","1190–1245":"1190–1245","1210–1270":"1210–1270","1190":"1190","1247":"1247","1245":"1245","before 1210":"avant 1210","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1270":"1270","Fisherton, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Fisherton, Ayrshire, Écosse","Forfarshire, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Forfarshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Dundaff Castle, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"David Graham est né en 1185, à Forfarshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Agnes Nobles. Il est décédé en 1247, à Fisherton, Ayrshire, Écosse, à l’âge de 62 ans."},"de":{"1185–1247":"1185–1247","1190–1245":"1190–1245","1210–1270":"1210–1270","1190":"1190","1247":"1247","1245":"1245","before 1210":"vor 1210","1210":"1210","1185":"1185","1270":"1270","Fisherton, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Fisherton, Ayrs